    "content": "{\n  \"narration\": \"Elder Mirna's eyes narrow with a trace of concern as you ask about recent rumors and unusual happenings. She leans forward and lowers her voice, keeping an eye on the windows in case curious villagers approach. \\\"Folk say the land is healing, but peace doesn't always come quickly, Norn. There've been tales of flickering lights out by the old keep—some claim it's the restless spirits lingering, others think bandits are searching for what the curse left behind.\\\"\\n\\nShe glances at the counter where a small bone charm sits—a roughly carved talisman strung with faded blue thread. \\\"And someone left that on my doorstep last night. No note, no tracks, just that thing. Some say it's a ward, others call it a warning. The truth is, nobody knows.\\\"\\n\\nMirna gestures to a narrow glass case on a side shelf, where several rare trinkets are displayed. You approach to examine them closely:\\n\\n- The first is a silvered thimble etched with tiny arcane runes—said to bring luck to any who sew or mend.\\n- Next sits a vial of what looks like shimmering dust, labeled 'Pixie Spark.' The label claims it can spark a fleeting, harmless illusion if blown into the air.\\n- There's a battered brass spyglass, well-used but still functional, the initials 'E.G.' scratched into the casing—perhaps belonging to a long-lost scout.\\n- Finally, a small wooden whistle carved in the shape of a crow; the wood is old but polished with care, and rumor claims it can sometimes call crows to your aid if blown at dusk.\\n\\nElder Mirna offers a knowing smile as you study each one. \\\"Most are keepsakes that found their way here over the years. They may not look like much, but in these parts, a little luck and a little faith go a long way. If any catch your eye, or if you want to know the stories behind them, you have only to ask.\\\"\",\n  \"actions\": [\n    {\n      \"action\": \"updatePlot\",\n      \"parameters\": {\n        \"plotPointId\": \"PP005\",\n