    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "{\n  \"narration\": \"Elder Mirna's expression grows thoughtful at your question. She glances toward the window and lowers her voice. \\\"The old mill's been abandoned since before I was born—its wheel long stilled, but the stones still stand. Most folk keep away. Those who do see the lights say they come just before midnight—soft, blue flickers like lanterns, moving slow as mist among the ruins. Young Tam and his friends dared each other to go last harvest, but they lost their nerve before getting close. Only Old Tommen claims to have seen shapes moving, but he won't go back, not for a barrel of ale. No one's found the courage to truly investigate—not since the curse.\\\"\\n\\nYou turn your attention to the faded parchment map in the glass case. Carefully lifting it, you examine the fragile surface. The map shows the familiar outline of Harrow's Hollow, the main roads, and the neighboring forest. Near the mill's location, a series of cryptic symbols have been inked: a spiral, a trio of small crosses, and what appears to be a crescent moon. Along the forest's edge, a dotted line weaves toward the mill, then disappears into a thicket marked by a sketch of twisted trees. Faded text reads, \\\"Watch the shadows where water runs dry.\\\"\\n\\nElder Mirna watches your inspection. \\\"That map turned up in a crate from the old Greymont estate. No one in town knows who drew it, but some say it matches stories from the founding days—a time when the mill was more than a place for grinding grain. If those markings mean something, it's lost to time or waiting for the right eyes.\\\"\\n\\nIs there a particular symbol you'd like to investigate, or would you like to ask about someone who might know more? Perhaps you wish to claim your reward—or risk a visit to the mill yourself?\",\n  \"actions\": [\n    {\n      \"action\": \"updateTime\",\n      \"parameters\": {\n        \"timeEstimate\": 2\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"action\": \"updatePlot\",\n      \"parameters\": {\n        \"plotPointId\": \"PP005\",\n        \"newStatus\": \"in progress\",\n        \"plotImpact\": \"Norn learns that the old mill is the source of mysterious lights and uninvestigated rumors, and examines a cryptic map possibly tied to the mill's secrets. Mirna reveals local fears and the lack of any true investigation, suggesting new leads for the hero.\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"
